[size=4]First I apologize for the bad english, I'm italiano.Lucerne ENB, was created to make the lighting of Skyrim as realistic as possible, and not only that, the colors are not altered too much, I tried to make them more or less balanced with the original ones, the lighting is inspired by that of ENB Opethfeldt, the nights are dark enough, but just install the mods torch or lantern, all to make the atmosphere more realistic, this is my first ENB that public here on the nexus, and this is the first version, so in the future there may be updates, I will support this ENB as long as possible, if you have any problem do not hesitate to ask questions, and I'll try to help you, thank you everyone who have made this possible, good FPS with both the preset extreme, both with that performance,if you want to add some videos, just ask,have fun....[/size]

[size=4]Lucerne ENB is very easy to install :

[/size][color=#ff0000][size=6]In version 2.0 does not have to install more Realistic lighting overhaul[/size][/color]

[size=4]- Download the rar file Lucerne ENB[/size]
[size=4]- Choose from preset extreme or performance (performance is not the DOF and ambient occlusion)[/size]
[size=4]- Extract all the root of skyrim[/size]
[size=4]- Download the latest binaries of http://enbdev.com/, I am using v0.279, and copy the files and        d3d9.dll enbhost.exe, and copy them to the root folder of skyrim
[/size]-  [size=4]Sure it is active file Lucerne Weather.esp[/size]
[size=4]- Have fun and enjoy[/size]

[color=#00ff00][size=6]To open the console of enb press ctrl + page down

[/size][/color][size=6]  [color=#ff00ff]O[/color][/size][color=#ff00ff][size=6]pen enblocal.ini the root of skyrim, and enable the   "FixParallaxBugs = false" to "FixParallaxBugs = [/size][/color][size=6]true[/size][color=#ff00ff][size=6]"[/size][/color]



[size=4][img]http://aninternetstore.com/includes/templates/images/neon_line.png[/img][/size]
[size=4][img]http://oi60.tinypic.com/2nh00nc.jpg[/img][/size]

[/size]
[size=4]- Vivid Clouds and Fogs[/size]
[size=4] 

[/size][/b][/font][font=Comic Sans MS][b][size=4] [/size][color=#ffff00][size=5]Edit your SkyrimPrefs.ini:[/size][/color]
[size=4]- fGamma=1.16000[/size]
[size=4]- bFloatPointRenderTarget=1[/size]
[size=4]- bDeferredShadows=1[/size]
[size=4]- bTreesReceiveShadows=1[/size]
[size=4]- bDrawLandShadows=1[/size]
[size=4]- bShadowsOnGrass=1[/size]
[color=#f1c232][size=4]- Disable Antialiasing and Anisotropic Filtering in your [/size][/color][/b][/font][b][color=#f1c232][size=4]graphics card's Control Panel[/size][/color][/b][font=Comic Sans MS][b]
